stylometry: When setting the level of safety stock, you must consider the estimated demand during lead time and the service level. Safety stock is basically additional inventory a company has in case of any emergencies, such has a delay in deliveries or a delay in production. This additional inventory is essential, that way the company does not run out of any inventory. It is important to know the estimated demand during lead time because this number may change, based on time of year, time of week, season, etc. It is important to know the demand, that way you know you have enough inventory, but not too much inventory, because then you will create holding costs. It is also important to know the service level as well. This gives you a percentage of the service, found out from the percentage of safety stock. For example, if there is 5% of safety stock, then the service level in 95%.
